ivardefs.name: approvalDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was approved by the publisher. Approval happens once when the content is officially approved for usage.

ivardefs.name: author_
ivardefs.desc: An individiual or organization primarily involved in the creation and maintenance of the content.

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: copyright
ivardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to the evidence and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the evidence.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the evidence was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the evidence changes.

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the evidence from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: editor_
ivardefs.desc: An individual or organization primarily responsible for internal coherence of the content.

ivardefs.name: effectivePeriod
ivardefs.desc: The period during which the evidence content was or is planned to be in active use.

ivardefs.name: endorser_
ivardefs.desc: An individual or organization responsible for officially endorsing the content for use in some setting.

ivardefs.name: exposureBackground
ivardefs.desc: A reference to a EvidenceVariable resource that defines the population for the research.

ivardefs.name: exposureVariant_
ivardefs.desc: A reference to a EvidenceVariable resource that defines the exposure for the research.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this evidence when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the evidence is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: lastReviewDate
ivardefs.desc: The date on which the resource content was last reviewed. Review happens periodically after approval but does not change the original approval date.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the evidence. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: note_
ivardefs.desc: A human-readable string to clarify or explain concepts about the resource.

ivardefs.name: outcome_
ivardefs.desc: A reference to a EvidenceVariable resomece that defines the outcome for the research.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the organization or individual that published the evidence.

ivardefs.name: relatedArtifact_
ivardefs.desc: Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references.

ivardefs.name: reviewer_
ivardefs.desc: An individual or organization primarily responsible for review of some aspect of the content.

ivardefs.name: shortTitle
ivardefs.desc: The short title provides an alternate title for use in informal descriptive contexts where the full, formal title is not necessary.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this evidence. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: subtitle
ivardefs.desc: An explanatory or alternate title for the Evidence giving additional information about its content.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the evidence.

ivardefs.name: topic_
ivardefs.desc: Descriptive topics related to the content of the Evidence. Topics provide a high-level categorization grouping types of Evidences that can be useful for filtering and searching.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this evidence when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance; also called its canonical identifier. This SHOULD be globally unique and SHOULD be a literal address at which at which an author

ivardefs.name: useContext_

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the evidence when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the evidence author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it

properties.desc: The Evidence resource describes the conditional state (population and any exposures being compared within the population) and outcome (if specified) that the knowledge (evidence, assertion, recommendation) is about.
